				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$T_\mathrm{B}$$\end{document}, which can exceed many hours at sufficiently low temperatures [13]. Usually, TB\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$T_\mathrm{B}$$\end{document} is defined as the temperature where the magnetization is retained for at least 100 s after removal of an external magnetic field. Above TB\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
