				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$V_\mathrm{sd}$$\end{document}, peaks in the conductance are observed when additional transport channels are getting opened. In the ground state [(first figure in (a)], the numbers of electrons on the QD is fixed and thus no electron transport takes place. b By adjusting the gate voltage Vg\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$V_\mathrm{g}$$\end{document}, oscillating regimes of conductance can be detected. A similar behavior is observed when Vsd\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
