				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$V_\mathrm{sd}$$\end{document}, so-called Coulomb-diamonds are obtained. d Co-tunneling processes occurring in QD devices with strong hybridization with the leads, which result in a conductance peak without any bias applied, denoted as Kondo ridge in (e). However, this effect vanishes when the QD does not carry a spin, i.e. it carries an even number of electrons.
Picture adapted from Ref. [86]. Reprinted with permission from Springer Nature

