				\begin{document}$$\hbox {Ga}_{\text {7}}$$\end{document}Zn host [161]. Depending on the probed transitions selected by different magnetic fields, phase-memory times of 870 ns, 660 ns and 580 ns were observed at 2.1 K. Embedding molecular magnets in diamagnetic matrices is thus a promising way to find new possible molecular that directly show quantum coherence in the solid state, albeit the total spin density is reduced.Fig. 28
